{
  "texts": [
    "RL aims to discover the optimal policy Ã * maximizing expected returns:Ã * = argmax π E[R|Ã].",
    "(1)In non-episodic MDPs (T = ∞), a µ < 1 ensures the finiteness of the reward sum, making full trajectory-based methods impracticable, but finite-transition methods viable [28].State-of-the-art RL techniques use Value-Based, Policy-Based, or Actor-Critic Methods.",
    "Value-Based MethodsIn the context of an agent operating under a specific policy Ã, we define the statevalue functionV π (s t) = E π [G t | S t = s],which represents the expected return from state s under policy Ã.",
    "This function captures the long-term value of being in a particular state while following the given policy.",
    "Similarly, the action-value function,Q π (s t, a t) = E π [G t | S t = s, A t = a],estimates the expected return of taking action a in state s according to policy Ã."
  ]
}